cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a new design for convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and evaluates its performance on image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the relationship between backpropagation (BP) and feedforward (FF) designs, which suggests that it could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The Saab transform introduced in the paper is a signal processing technique, which could make it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
